Description : Homo sapiens interleukin-4 (IL-4) gene, promoter region.
Organism : Homo sapiens
Accession Number : MH644812.1

IL-4 is a cytokine which is produced by activated T cells. 
It acts on the proliferation and differentiation of B and T lymphocytes.
It also enhances the function of natural killer cells, eosinophils, and mast cells. 
It plays a crucial role in promoting inflammatory responses.

